From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 11:12:19 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] vendor/n2: thread a logical build dir through filesystem
 access
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

n2 resolves every path against the process cwd, which forces the in-process
`ninja` builtin to chdir the engine to build a tree elsewhere — unusable when
recipes (and sibling builds) share the process. Add a thread-local logical
build dir (graph::set_cwd / get_cwd / resolve_cwd) that every filesystem touch
resolves relative paths against: stat (graph), build-file and depfile reads
(scanner::read_file_with_nul), the .n2_db (db::open + its parent-dir create in
load), response files (task::write_rspfile), and output directories
(work::create_parent_dirs). Default (None) is the process cwd — unchanged.

Each recipe runs on a fresh worker thread, so Runner::start carries the dir
across the thread boundary (get_cwd before spawn, set_cwd inside) so the
recipe's executor, rspfile writes, and depfile reads all see it.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01XyA6FzC6QGgsrjEYEBJV46
